MkDocs Commands




mkdocs new [dir-name]
 - Create a new project.


mkdocs serve
 - Start the live-reloading docs server.


mkdocs build
 - Build the documentation site.


mkdocs help
 - Print this help message.




Project layout

docs/
    index.md  # The documentation homepage.
    ...       # Other markdown pages, images and other files.

    index.html# The generated HTML homepage.
    ...       # other generated pages.

docs.text:
1. Performance Test Objectives


The objectives of the  application performance test are to:




Verify the functionality of the  application.


Establish a baseline for the  application without concurrent performance testing on the  server. This would correlate to purging during off-peak hours.


Establish a baseline for the  application concurrent with performance testing of the  server. This would correlate to purging during peak hours. 


Provide metrics describing the impact of processing to the  user base; this data will serve as the basis for determining the  schedule.




2. Performance Test Strategy


The performance test will be conducted in the Staging environment located in DC-1 and will consist of three primary test scenarios.  




Verification of Process


Assess Performance


Assess Performance while is running 




The initial test will be conducted with the Test Group I set of cases in order to verify that the application is deleting all required database and file system objects. Once this verification is completed, the test will continue to assess performance of the application as well as any impact on the performance of the application while is running. 




3. Participants and Contributors
